<br>
The military does teach you discipline, patience, and promotes self-esteem after they rip it away from in Basic Training. And if you join the Marines, you'll be the butt of every stupid joke the military ever invented. There's a reason the two GI's were making fun of the Marines in Hamburger Hill, when the truck driver was trying to get rid of a trailer. &quot;find a Marine to sign for it&quot; &quot;yeah, those dumb f$%#ers will do anything&quot;<br>
<br>
A sailor and a marine walk out into an alley, behind a bar, to urinate. When they're done, the Marine looks at the Sailor and says &quot;In the Marines, they teach us to wash our hands after pissing&quot; the sailor replies&quot;In the Navy, they teach us not to piss on our hands&quot;<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
