It's NONE of those things.  I was in the Marine Corps.. there were MANY times when I did not get fed in order to complete my job and would have to spend my own money for food.<br>
<br>
You spend alot of time in the field.. and only one of those times was there ever a roof over my head (and that a tent roof)<br>
<br>
I learned something.. how to count bullets.  They put me in the job they needed people in, and I did it, but come to find out when I'm a civilian again I don't even qualify for a warehouse job because the civilians use computers and scanners and such and in the Corps we used good old papers and index cards.<br>
<br>
Also.. I was put on anti-depressants and summarily separated from the Marine Corps.  I also saw lots of people get out early for medical reasons.. admin separation.  It isn't exactly job security unless you stay in your tip-top shape, something not as easy to do with the strenuous lifestyle.<br>
<br>
I'm with Shin here - go to college. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roninsenshi>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia<br>Jihad on that ass!</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/24/03 5:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> You have to be motivated, you have to desire to always be the best, always in competition.. if you aren't the best then you'll never be good enought. .. If you aren't in that mindset, if you're lazy or something, then don't join..<br>
